          <span class="ln"><span>who <em>ships.</em></span></span>
        </h2>
        <p class="deck">A product marketer who builds the systems instead of only briefing them - the agents, the sites and the SEO behind <b>657K+ leads</b> and <b>18M+ in organic traffic</b>.</p>
        <p class="byline">By <b>Swapnil Biswas</b> - Senior Product Marketing Manager, LambdaTest</p>
        <div class="cols">
          <p>Most product marketers stop at the deck. Swapnil Biswas starts there and keeps going - into the codebase, the crawl budget and the automation layer that actually moves the numbers. He is a PMM and growth strategist who codes AI agents, ships production sites and runs technical SEO himself.</p>
          <p>The thesis is simple. Positioning that nobody can execute is a slide. So he builds the execution: twenty-plus AI agents and internal tools shipped, a self-hosted portfolio that scores 95 to 100 on Lighthouse, and an organic engine that has compounded into millions of visits.</p>
          <p>The result reads less like a marketer's resume and more like an operator's ledger. Leads in the hundreds of thousands. Traffic in the tens of millions. Conversion lifted tenfold. The decks still get written - they just describe systems that already exist.</p>
          <div class="leadcta">
            <a class="btn solid" href="#filings">Read the filings <span class="ar">&#8599;</span></a>
            <a class="btn outline" href="#classified">Get in touch</a>
